==Item Data==

Items are stored in Bank 00 with prices and bonuses in several tables:

'''Item Categories:'''
* '''Weapons''' ($00-$06): Bamboo Pole (+2 ATK) through Erdrick's Sword (+40 ATK)
* '''Armor''' ($07-$0D): Clothes (+2 DEF) through Erdrick's Armor (+28 DEF)
* '''Shields''' ($0E-$10): Small Shield (+4 DEF) through Silver Shield (+20 DEF)
* '''Tools''' ($11+): Herbs (restore 23-30 HP), Keys, Wings, Magic Items

'''Price Table''' (Bank 00, $9947-$9990):
* 2 bytes per item (little-endian)
* Sell price = Buy price / 2
* Quest items have no price ($0000)

'''Bonus Tables''' (Bank 00, $99CF-$99FE):
* Weapon Attack Bonuses: $99CF-$99DE (16 bytes)
* Armor Defense Bonuses: $99DF-$99EE (16 bytes)
* Shield Defense Bonuses: $99EF-$99FE (16 bytes)

See [[Dragon Warrior (NES) - Values|Values]] for complete item lists and prices.

==Map Data==

Map structure varies by type:

'''Overworld:'''
* Size: 120×120 tiles (14,400 tiles total)
* Storage: Compressed row pointers (Bank 00, $A653)
* Tile properties: Walkability, encounter rates, terrain type
* Special tiles: Town/castle entrances, caves, bridges

'''Interior Maps''' (towns, castles, dungeons):
* Size: 10×10 to 32×32 tiles
* Storage: Uncompressed tile data
* Each map has header: pointer, width, height, boundary block type

'''Map Header Format:'''
{| class="wikitable"
!  Offset  !!  Size  !!  Description
|-
|  +$00  ||  2 bytes  ||  Pointer to map data
|-
|  +$02  ||  1 byte  ||  Width in blocks
|-
|  +$03  ||  1 byte  ||  Height in blocks
|-
|  +$04  ||  1 byte  ||  Boundary block ID
|}

'''Map Type Flags''' (stored in RAM $16):
* $00 = Overworld
* $10 = Town/Castle
* $20 = Cave/Dungeon

