==Game Formulas==

===Battle Formulas===

'''Physical Damage:'''
* Player → Enemy: (Player ATK / 2) - (Enemy DEF / 4) + Random(0, 4)
* Enemy → Player: (Enemy STR / 2) - (Player DEF / 4) + Random(0, 4)
* Minimum damage: 0 (cannot be negative)

'''Critical Hits:'''
* Chance: Player AGI / 64 (out of 256)
* Damage: Normal Damage × 2

'''Hit/Miss:'''
* Player Base: 224/256 (87.5%) - (Enemy AGI / 4)
* Enemy Base: 192/256 (75%) - (Player AGI / 2)

'''Dodge:'''
* Chance: Player AGI / 4 (out of 256)

See [[Dragon Warrior (NES) - Battle System|Battle System]] for complete battle mechanics.

===Experience and Level Formulas===

'''Stat Growth:'''
* HP: Base table value + Random(0, 3) per level
* MP: Base table value + Random(0, 2) per level
* STR (even levels): Random(2, 4)
* STR (odd levels): Random(1, 3)
* AGI (odd levels): Random(2, 5)
* AGI (even levels): Random(1, 3)

'''Spell Learning:'''
* Fixed levels: 3(HEAL), 4(HURT), 7(SLEEP), 9(RADIANT), 10(STOPSPELL), 12(OUTSIDE), 13(RETURN), 15(REPEL), 17(HEALMORE), 19(HURTMORE)

See [[Dragon Warrior (NES) - Experience System|Experience System]] for complete progression tables.

===Spell Formulas===

'''Healing:'''
* HEAL: Random(10, 17) HP, 4 MP
* HEALMORE: Random(85, 100) HP, 10 MP

'''Damage:'''
* HURT: Random(5, 12) - (Enemy DEF / 8), 2 MP, minimum 1
* HURTMORE: Random(58, 65) - (Enemy DEF / 4), 5 MP, minimum 1

'''Status Effects:'''
* SLEEP: 160/256 base - (Enemy Level × 2), min 32/256, 2 MP
* STOPSPELL: 160/256 base - (Enemy Level × 3), min 16/256, 2 MP

'''Utility:'''
* RADIANT: 3 tile radius, 3 MP, permanent until map change
* REPEL: 127 steps, 2 MP, zero encounters
* OUTSIDE: 6 MP, warp to dungeon exit
* RETURN: 8 MP, warp to Tantegel (43, 43)

See [[Dragon Warrior (NES) - Values|Values]] for all spell data.

===Encounter System===

'''Encounter Rates by Terrain:'''
* Tantegel area: 16/256 (6.25%), check every 8 steps
* Grassland: 32/256 (12.5%)
* Forest: 48/256 (18.75%)
* Hills: 64/256 (25%)
* Mountains: 80/256 (31.25%)
* Swamp: 96/256 (37.5%)

'''Flee Success:'''
* Base: 192/256 (75%)
* Bonus: (Player AGI - Enemy AGI) / 4
* Range: 64/256 (25%) to 224/256 (87.5%)

See [[Dragon Warrior (NES) - Monster Data|Monster Data]] for encounter tables by area.

